Investigations indicate that LLMs' performance significantly deteriorates when dealing with random Wikidata facts, specifically those associated with long-tail entities, in comparison to popular entities, as evidenced in the PopQA dataset [mallen2023trust] and other datasets [petroniLAMA2019,wdknown]. 
This effect can be traced back to a causal relationship between the frequency of an entity's appearance in the pre-training corpus and the LLMs' capacity for memorization [elazar2023measuring]. Even sizable LLMs face difficulties when trying to retain information about long-tail entities [kandpal2022large]. KGs inherently present an advantage over LLMs through their provision of knowledge about long-tail entities [kalo2022kamel,wdknown] and thus can further help improve the recall for Knowledge Computing tasks.